description.narrative: In 2019, the coverage of key nutrition services has continued to increase with Government ownership. Following formal release of Public Expenditure Review on Nutrition, financial tracking system is being designed to increase funding for the nutrition. UNICEF also increased private sector engagement to improve maternity benefits and exclusive breastfeeding through Mothers@work. An urban nutrition minimum package for nutrition services was defined. Between 2017 to 2019 stunting has declined from 31% to 28%. While is this encouraging, wasting has not changed and is high at 14%,one of the focus of 2020 is to develop community-based strategy on the prevention of wasting. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
